-- Chilean Stocks: Besalco, E-CL, Ripley Corp and Sigdo Koppers
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-07-13T20:56:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/chile-stocks-banco-de-chile-e-cl-besalco-vapores-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  rose 0.4 percent to 4,372.67. The  MSCI Chile
index (MXCL)  advanced 1.2 percent to 2,434.88.  Besalco SA (BESALCO)   increased 2.1 percent to 815.11
pesos, ending an eight-day losing streak. Banco Santander SA
added Chile’s second-largest construction company to its list of
favorite Chilean small-capitalization stocks.  E-CL SA (ECL)   fell 1.3 percent to 1,118.3 pesos, its
lowest closing price in 11 months. Northern Chile’s largest
power generator was cut to hold from buy at BICE Inversiones.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)   fell 2.4 percent to 439.7 pesos,
its lowest price in nine months and leading losses among members
of the Ipsa benchmark index. Banco Santander SA dropped the
department store operator from its list of favorite Chilean
stocks, saying it would be more affected than its peers by the
government’s plan to cap consumer loan interest rates.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   advanced 3 percent to 1,180 pesos,
the biggest increase in a month. Santiago-based brokerage IM
Trust SA said yesterday it added the Chilean industrial holding
company to its list of five favorite local stocks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
